summary: This agreement outlines the sale of a collection (specified in Attachment A) from a Seller to an Institution for a stated purchase price.  The Institution will pay upon satisfactory inspection, and the Seller is responsible for shipping and risk of loss until arrival.  Intellectual property rights transfer (or are dedicated to the public domain, or reserved with specified uses as detailed in Attachment B) depending on the chosen clause.  The Institution has 90 days to inspect and can reject items with payment adjustments or replacements.  The Seller indemnifies the Institution against any claims arising from breaches of warranty.
